Deposit Guaranty National Banksaid it will add 8.1 mln dlrs to its loan loss reserve duringthe second quarter to cover potential foreign debt exposure inLatin America.    It said the action will reduce second quarter earnings ofDeposit Guaranty Corp, the bank's parent, by about 60 cts ashare.    It said the corporation will have a profitable quarter andalso a strong earnings year in 1987.    Following the increase, Deposit Guaranty said its loan lossreserve will total about 37 mln dlrs, or 1.9 pct of totaloutstanding loans. Reuter&#3;